The paper deals with the problem of joint cluster analysis and outlier detection, which is a common topic in machine learning and data mining. The proposed algorithm involves the use of objective functions and binary matrices, which are commonly used in the sub-fields of machine learning and data mining such as clustering (cs.LG), data mining (cs.DM), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and databases (cs.DB). Additionally, the paper discusses the effectiveness of the proposed algorithm in detecting anomalies, which is a topic in computer security (cs.CR). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG, cs.DM, cs.AI, cs.DB, and cs.CR.
